Target: An ontology developed for design of experiment.

Comment: A procedure to plan and define the conditions for performing controlled experimental trials. [doi:10.1016/j.compchemeng.2017.05.010]
A method to propose conditions for controlled experimental trials.
"Thompson sampling efficient multiobjective optimization" strategy proposed in paper doi:10.1007/s10898-018-0609-2.
"Latin hypercube sampling" strategy.
Criterion is used to construct the LHS design. It tells LHS how to sample the points. [Surrogate Modeling Toolbox]
A criterion that centers the points within the sampling intervals.
A criterion maximises the minimum distance between points, but places the point in a randomised location within its interval.
A criterion same as the criterion "Maximin", but centered within the intervals.
A criterion minimises the maximum correlation coefficient.
The space bounded by the upper and lower limits of a set of design variables.
A variable to be defined for controlled experimental trials.
A design variable that is continuous in domain.
A design variable that is discrete in domain.
A parameter that is fixed in design domain.
The outcome collected during controlled experimental trails.
A complete recording of controlled experimental trails done in the past.
A relation between a chemical reaction and its design of experiment template for optimisation.
A relation between a design of experiment excersise and the chemical reaction it is optimising.
A relation between a design of experiment exercise and the strategy it uses.
A relation between a design of experiment exercise and the domain where it is constrained.
A relation between a domain and the design variable it consists of.
A relation between a domain and the fix parameters it consists of.
A relation between a design of experiment exercise and the system response it collects.
A relation between a design of experiment exercise and any historical data it utilised.
A relation between a design of experiment exercise and the new experiment it defines.
A relation between a continuous variable/a system response/a fixed parameter in a design of experiment exercise and the dimensional quantity it refers to.
A relation between previous experiment records/future experiment conditions and the reaction experiment it refers to.
An attribute indicates the upper limit of a continuous variable.
An attribute indicates the lower limit of a continuous variable.

An attribute to provide unique identification of a design variable/a system response/a fixed parameter within a design of experiment exercise. It should be used when multiple these instances within one design of experiment exercise are instantiated from the same concept.
An attribute to indicate the direction of the optimisation of a system response in a design of experiment exercise.
The number of new experiments to be suggested based on the historical data in a design of experiment exercise. Defualt is 1.

Number of retries to use for spectral sampling iF the singular value decomposition fails. Retrying chooses a new Monte Carlo sampling which usually fixes the problem. Defualt is 10. [https://gosummit.readthedocs.io/en/latest/strategies.html#tsemo]

Number of spectral points used in spectral sampling. Default is 1500. Note that the Matlab TSEMO version uses 4000 which will improve accuracy but significantly slow down optimisation speed. [https://gosummit.readthedocs.io/en/latest/strategies.html#tsemo]
Number of generations used in the internal optimisation with NSGAII. Default is 100. [https://gosummit.readthedocs.io/en/latest/strategies.html#tsemo]
Population size used in the internal optimisation with NSGAII. Default is 100. [https://gosummit.readthedocs.io/en/latest/strategies.html#tsemo]
An attribute indicates the random state of LHS sampling.
